    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nWhen calling exec() inside a 'def' statement, local variables inside function definition cannot be dereferenced by exec() if globals/locals arguments of exec is left empty, eg. using default 'None'\r\n\r\nThe example code will show \"NameError: name 'hi' is not defined\" instead of printing \"hello\"\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\r\ndef say_hi():\r\n\thi = 'hello'\r\n\texec('print(hi)')\r\n\r\nsay_hi()\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nhello\n\n### OS\n\nmacOS\n\n### Python version\n\n3.9.6\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.0.2\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
